refentry:
elements secondaryie secondaryie Element
secondaryie &secondaryie.purpose;
&secondaryie.synopsis.gen; Description
SecondaryIE identifies a secondary word or words in an IndexEntry.
In IndexEntrys, you can specify as many secondary terms that are necessary. Secondary and tertiary terms can be mixed, following the primary.
Processing expectations
&format.block; SecondaryIEs occur below the PrimaryIE, usually aligned with each other and indented from the primary.
&FutureChanges;
&fu.interfacedefinition;
&secondaryie.parents.gen; &secondaryie.children.gen;
Attributes
linkends
Linkends, if used, points to the IndexTerms indexed by this entry.
See Also &secondaryie.seealso.gen;
Examples
For examples, see &secondaryie.example.seealso.gen;.
